The EiffelCOM Wizard can generate a project to reuse or create a COM component. It can create a new COM component from either an existing Eiffel project or a COM defintion file.
New COM component from existing Eiffel project
New COM component from COM definition file
Client application to access an existing component
A definition file is either a Interface Definition file (*.idl) or a type library file (*.tlb). A type library can be linked into a component (*.ocx, *.dll, *.exe, ...)

COM components can be accessed either via Automation or the interfaces virtual tables. When accessing a component via its interfaces virtual tables, there are two ways of encoding arguments and results: * Using the universal marshaller. This is the easiest way but not all data types are supported. * Using a custom marshaller. This option requires a marshaller DLL.
Virtual table and the universal marshaller
Virtual table and a custom marshaller
By default the EiffelCOM wizard compiles the generated Eiffel and C code. Compiling the Eiffel code requires compiling the C code.
By default the EiffelCOM Wizard stops on compilation error.
Do not stop on compilation error
